tiated. The immediate practical challenge that emerges clearly from the contributions to this book is the need to continue to support initiatives to build trust and cooperation at the regional level in Southeast Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHijacking of shipszSoutheast Asia. 0aPirateszSoutheast Asia. 0aTerrorism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh1 aChaikin, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDjalal, Hasjim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Derek, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMukundan, P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOng, Graham Gerard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPladdet, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValencia, Mark J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValencia, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValencia, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aYoung, Adam J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060668340uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981230589340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789812305893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789812305893.jpg  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-